<br>
1.) Assuming you are level 57 and have PoF, mana pres 3, and KEI, you are not going to run out of mana. Even if snare resists and you have to snare that one, then resnare all, you will still not.<br>
2.) Their pop time is roughly 7-8 minutes (I have timed exactly). Even if you run down to 5% mana left after the quad, after harvesting, with KEI, you med back to approx. 80% mana by the time they repop.<br>
3.) At 80% you are good to go - after getting them out of the tunnel, rounded up, and snared, you will be 90%+, which <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be enough to finish.<br>
4.) So considering the pop time is set and out of your control, and perfectly complements your mana regen, the only thing left to speed the process along is how fast you kill them... I.E - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>DON'T</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> make it take twice as long by using your horse, especially since the extra mana you're getting doesn't translate to dick as long you are at the perfect amount of mana by the time they're back up anyway! Let alone the fact that you will have to snare twice if you're on your pony.<br>
<br>
Just for kicks I tried PoD flies today again.. ROFL is it considered a successful quad when you pull 5 flies, then in trying to get enough room to fetter one, you aggro a diseased rat, which stuns you, making you meat for 5 flies headed your way?! In short.. the GD camp r0x for nice steady, NOT death-enducing XP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=630472" target="top">Oaklenia Somesweetlastname</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
